<paragraph blockId="59.[151,1436,1350,2033]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,487,1504,1530]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Diagnostic description.</emphasis>
Shining; head, pronotum, antennae, tibiae and tarsi dark reddish brown; elytra, venter and femora yellowish brown, elytral apices darker. Length of pronotum + elytra = 2.8 mm (male), 2.8 mm (females). Head finely punctate. Pronotum broad, widest at base, sides rounded, basal angles obtuse; ratio length:width = 1:1.7; finely punctate with faint reticulate microsculpture. Elytra short, wider than pronotum, ratio length:width = 1:0.8; with 9 regular, closely punctate striae; striae 6 and 7 do not reach apex, stria 8 does not reach base, stria 1 weakly impressed; intervals minutely punctate, transversely striolate. Antennal club (
<figureCitation box="[159,260,1737,1763]" captionStart="FIGURES 172–175" captionStartId="60.[151,271,1049,1073]" captionTargetBox="[256,1342,354,1013]" captionTargetId="figure-350@60.[244,1342,351,1022]" captionTargetPageId="60" captionText="FIGURES 172–175. Platyhydnobius newtonorum. 172. Right antenna, dorsal view. 173. Aedeagus, dorsal view. 174. Female sternite 8, ventral view. 175. Female coxites and styli, ventral view. Scale bar = 0.3 mm (Fig. 175), 0.4 mm (Figs. 173, 174), 0.5 mm (Fig. 172)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5311016" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5311016/files/figure.png" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Fig. 172</figureCitation>
) moderately slender, ratio club width:length = 1:3.1; width ratio of antennomeres 7:8:9 = 1.2:1:1.6. Left mandible with subapical tooth; right mandible with tooth on apical one-half of inner margin. In both sexes, all femora unarmed; all tibiae slender, spinose on outer margin, protibiae and mesotibiae weakly widened apically, male mesotibia weakly curved. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[763,835,1852,1878]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Male.</emphasis>
Aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[982,1086,1853,1879]" captionStart="FIGURES 172–175" captionStartId="60.[151,271,1049,1073]" captionTargetBox="[256,1342,354,1013]" captionTargetId="figure-350@60.[244,1342,351,1022]" captionTargetPageId="60" captionText="FIGURES 172–175. Platyhydnobius newtonorum. 172. Right antenna, dorsal view. 173. Aedeagus, dorsal view. 174. Female sternite 8, ventral view. 175. Female coxites and styli, ventral view. Scale bar = 0.3 mm (Fig. 175), 0.4 mm (Figs. 173, 174), 0.5 mm (Fig. 172)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5311016" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5311016/files/figure.png" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Fig. 173</figureCitation>
) with median lobe elongate, narrowed apically to small rounded tip. Parameres longer than median lobe, flat, with small lateral lobes near base. Paramere apices thin, expanded before acute tips, with two dorsal setae and many small setae apically. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,249,1968,1994]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Female.</emphasis>
Coxites (
<figureCitation box="[362,461,1969,1995]" captionStart="FIGURES 172–175" captionStartId="60.[151,271,1049,1073]" captionTargetBox="[256,1342,354,1013]" captionTargetId="figure-350@60.[244,1342,351,1022]" captionTargetPageId="60" captionText="FIGURES 172–175. Platyhydnobius newtonorum. 172. Right antenna, dorsal view. 173. Aedeagus, dorsal view. 174. Female sternite 8, ventral view. 175. Female coxites and styli, ventral view. Scale bar = 0.3 mm (Fig. 175), 0.4 mm (Figs. 173, 174), 0.5 mm (Fig. 172)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5311016" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5311016/files/figure.png" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Fig. 175</figureCitation>
) elongate, narrow, with apical and subapical setae; styli elongate, inserted at apices of coxites. Sternite 8 (
<figureCitation box="[409,509,2007,2033]" captionStart="FIGURES 172–175" captionStartId="60.[151,271,1049,1073]" captionTargetBox="[256,1342,354,1013]" captionTargetId="figure-350@60.[244,1342,351,1022]" captionTargetPageId="60" captionText="FIGURES 172–175. Platyhydnobius newtonorum. 172. Right antenna, dorsal view. 173. Aedeagus, dorsal view. 174. Female sternite 8, ventral view. 175. Female coxites and styli, ventral view. Scale bar = 0.3 mm (Fig. 175), 0.4 mm (Figs. 173, 174), 0.5 mm (Fig. 172)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5311016" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5311016/files/figure.png" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Fig. 174</figureCitation>
) rounded apically; anterior apophysis moderately broad, truncate apically.
</paragraph>
